item.title: Tryhackme writeup: Brainpan
item.description: Brainpan is part of the “Offensive Pentesting Path” in TryHackMe, and it is a straight-forward buffer overflow activity with further extra steps to achieve full privilege escalation. Note: This writeup doesn’t explain with full detail the whole exploitation process, and will skip a couple steps, but it serves as a “nudge” to the right direction when attempting this room. Initial Recon For system enumeration I used threader3000, finding ports 9999 and 10000 open.
